.TH NETWATCHD 1 "2026-07-14" "0.1.0" "NetWatch Daemon Manual"
.SH NAME
netwatchd \- Background daemon for network usage statistics monitoring
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B netwatchd
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B netwatchd
runs in the background to periodically collect network interface statistics
from sysfs (/sys/class/net) or /proc/net/dev. Collected samples are stored,
aggregated into minute/hourly/daily tiers, and cleaned up according to the
configured retention policy.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-c, \-\-config \fIPATH\fR
Specify a custom configuration file path.
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Print help information and exit.
.TP
.B \-V, \-\-version
Print version information and exit.
.SH SIGNALS
.TP
.B SIGTERM, SIGINT
Graceful shutdown. Closes database and terminates sampling loop.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/netwatch/config.toml
The configuration file.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/netwatch/netwatch.db
The SQLite WAL database storing historical network samples.
